						               													<description>Every seven summers the druid games take place. In them, druids from different areas use their skills to command creatures in tactical confrontations. (No animals or legendary creatures are harmed in the games)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Druid Games is a simple card game (played with a 54 card deck) in which each player will play combinations of cards across five terrains. The druid that is victorious in three or more of them is proclaimed the winner of that edition of the Druid Games. Different creatures have specific characteristics (fly, swim, walk) that might limit the terrains in which they can be played. Additionally special cards allows some 'druid magic' to take place. Yes, you can give wings to a walrus to have a flying walrus.&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;Each turn a player will place a creature card on one of the five terrains and, if desired, play special cards to produce 'druid magic' effects. The game will finish after all creature cards have been played (15 turns). The winner will be the druid that is victorious in three or more terrains.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
